  <p><img src="images/MikeMoore_8774_White_0.jpg" class="img-thumbnail" alt="MikeMore"width="300" height="200" align="left"><h2><center>DR MIKE MORE</center></h2></p><center><p>Chairman</p></center>
    <div class="container text-center">
    <p>Mike became Chair of PMC on 01 November 2016. He joined the PMC board of directors in September 2012 bringing extensive experience from health, police, transport as well as local government. He was chief executive for Westmoreland City Council until the end of 2013. Mike began his career at the National Audit Office in 1981. He was senior auditor at St Ann  Council in 1986 moving on to a number of increasingly high-level positions at the council including head of finance. Mike was appointed as the director of resource management of Portmore Council in 1999, and progressed to the position of chief executive in 2002 joining Westmoreland City Council as chief executive in April 2008. 
Mike’s non-executive roles include non-executive director on the Joint Venture Board for the University Campus Suffolk, plus positions as chair for the Prince’s Trust for Suffolk and the East of England Regional Chief Executives’ Group. He is also chair of the Central London Resilience Panel which includes all agencies including health and manages emergency planning. 
Mike also held a representative role on the Boys and Girls Championship Board. He has an active interest in developing the Health and Well-Being Board in central Kingston and the integration of health and social care. 
Mike holds a PhD from the University of the West Indies </p>
